    "text": "From a healthcare payer’s perspective, measuring insurance coverage ratios is a critical exercise in Risk Management and Market Analysis. Understanding these percentages allows organizations to:\n\nAssess Market Share: Identifying the ratio of active vs. inactive plans helps payers understand their penetration within a specific demographic or geographic region.\nPredict Financial Liability: High coverage ratios across expensive clinical paths (like chronic disease management) allow for more accurate actuarial modeling and premium pricing.\nIdentify Under-served Segments: By tracking the “No Insurance” demographic, payers can identify opportunities for new, more accessible product offerings or public-private partnerships.\nMonitor Operational Efficiency: A declining trend in coverage often correlates with rising out-of-pocket burdens, which can lead to higher rates of claim denials or delayed care—ultimately increasing long-term costs."
