    "section": "",
    "text": "FHIR (Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources) is a standard framework created by HL7 designed to facilitate the exchange of electronic health records. Unlike older standards, FHIR is built on modern web technologies—specifically a RESTful API—making it easier for different healthcare systems to share data seamlessly. It breaks down clinical data into modular “Resources,” such as Patients, Encounters, and Observations. By using a standardized format, healthcare providers can ensure that data captured in one system is accurately interpreted by another, which is critical for patient safety and data-driven clinical decision-making."
