    "section": "Strategic Advantages of the Claims Model",
    "text": "Strategic Advantages of the Claims Model\nThis data model provides three distinct advantages for healthcare administrators and insurance payers:\n\nGranular Cost Attribution: Instead of looking at a flat spreadsheet of “Total Spend,” payers can see exactly which disease-city combinations are most expensive. This allows for hyper-local resource allocation.\nIdentification of “High-Utilization” Hubs: By observing the width of the bars in the city branches, administrators can identify where patient encounters are most frequent, helping to plan future clinic expansions.\nPayer-Mix Transparency: The model clearly highlights the “Payer Mix” (the ratio of private insurance, government insurance, and uninsured) for specific conditions. This is vital for assessing the financial risk of a specific patient population."
