    "text": "Why Synthea is the Ideal Framework for This Model\nThe use of Synthea to build this model offers unique technical benefits that real-world data often cannot provide:\n\nNative FHIR Integration: Synthea is designed to generate data that is 100% compliant with the FHIR (Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources) standard. This ensures that the data model we see here can be easily integrated with modern hospital APIs.\nLongitudinal Patient Journeys: Unlike “snapshot” hospital data, Synthea simulates a patient from birth to death. This allows the decomposition tree to reflect true historical claims over time.\nRisk-Free Development: Because the data is synthetic, we can build complex visualizations and share them on this website without any risk of exposing Protected Health Information (PHI)."
